Package: freeamp
Version: 2.1.1
Revision: 1
Source: http://www.freeamp.org/download/src/%n-%v.tar.gz
SourceDirectory: %n
UpdateConfigGuess: true
Patch: %f.patch
BuildDepends: libvorbis, libogg, libmusicbrainz, gdk-pixbuf, freetype, gtk+
Depends: gdk-pixbuf-shlibs, zlib, gtk+, freetype-shlibs || freetype-hinting-shlibs, esound-shlibs, dlcompat, libmusicbrainz
DocFiles: AUTHORS CHANGES COPYING ChangeLog INSTALL NEWS README* help/unix/freeamphelp.tar.gz 
SetCFLAGS: -I%p/include/orbit-1.0/
SetLDFLAGS: -no-cpp-precomp
SetCPPFLAGS: -no-cpp-precomp
ConfigureParams: --enable-cmdline --enable-mp3prof --disable-x86opts --enable-shared
Description: An MP3/Vorbis/CD Audio player/Jukebox
DescDetail: <<
FreeAmp is an MP3/Vorbis/CD Audio player/Jukebox for Linux and Win32.
It features both graphical theme and text-based user interfaces, a
download manager for automating MP3 downloads, and a powerful music 
browser/playlist manager. Other features include HTTP/RTP streaming
playback with HTTP stream saving and title streaming, and a fast,
clean-sounding Open Source decoding engine. It supports Win32/OSS sound
systems, ALSA, and EsounD.
<<
